  <ab><lb n="1"/>  <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><orig n="unresolved">υ</orig> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="πάππος">πάππος</w> <w lemma="αὐτός">αὐτοῦ</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">μ</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Αὐρηλία"><expan><abbr>Αὐ<space unit="character" extent="1"/>ρ</abbr><ex>ηλία</ex></expan></name> <name nymRef="#Κωμική">Κωμικὴ</name> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἑρμίας">Ἑρμείου</name></persName></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="μήτηρ">μ<supplied reason="lost">ητὴρ</supplied></w>  <w lemma="αὐτός"><supplied reason="lost">αὐτοῦ</supplied></w>  <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  </ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>  his grandfather and M<gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">and</supplied> Aur(elia) Komike (daughter of) Hermeios, his m<supplied reason="lost">other</supplied>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>It is probable that the text is listing those who have been or will be buried in the sarcophagus, the first name to survive being that of the owner's grandfather, and since l .2 gives almost certainly the name of his mother, the intervening one was, no doubt, his father, who may well have been a Marcus Aurelius.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" n="none">
